Implement the `render()` method that draws the side-by-side diff view.

Layout (given `rows` and `cols` from render arguments):
- Row 0: Header bar — subtask name, index (e.g., "1/5"), and approval status
- Row 1: File path header (one per file, rendered as separator when scrolling through)
- Rows 2..rows-2: Two-column diff view
  - Left column: old version (width = (cols-3)/2), lines prefixed with `-` for deletions
  - Separator: ` │ ` (3 chars)
  - Right column: new version (width = remaining), lines prefixed with `+` for additions
- Last row: Key hints — `[a] Approve  [←/→] Prev/Next  [scroll] Mouse  [q] Quit`

Color scheme (ANSI escape codes):
- Deletions: red foreground (`\x1b[31m`) with `-` prefix
- Additions: green foreground (`\x1b[32m`) with `+` prefix
- Context lines: default foreground, space prefix
- Header/file paths: bold (`\x1b[1m`)
- Approved badge: green background

Scrolling: track `scroll_offset` in state; render only lines `scroll_offset..scroll_offset+visible_rows`. Clamp to bounds.